OL,7,FHe said the Home Office would not want
OL,8,Fa situation where it has "further
OL,9,F"reasons why it cannot be giving out
OL,10,Ffast decisions and compensation to
OL,11,Fpeople who have been terribly affected
OL,12,Fas a result of the scandal, and so
OL,13,Fthis movement, I think, would
OL,14,Finevitably cause some of that slowing
OL,15,Fdown, and I think that is something
OL,16,Fthat we have to be aware of".
OL,18,FHe said he had already pressed on the
OL,19,Fminister the need for guarantees
OL,20,Faround pension losses being covered by
OL,21,Fthe scheme.
