OL,7,FAsked to describe the level of trust
OL,8,Fin the Home Office currently among
OL,9,Fthose affected by the scandal, he
OL,10,Fsaid: "I'm afraid I still feel that
OL,11,Fthere is apprehension and some
OL,12,Fsuspicion with regards to, 'is this
OL,13,Fworking towards better outcomes?'
OL,15,F"What we need to accelerate is the
OL,16,Factions and activities that are going
OL,17,Fto build trust. I always say 'you
OL,18,Fcan't cross a bridge until you've
OL,19,Fbuilt it.'"
OL,26,@rD@GOUwD@AOU{D@KO]
